
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dfu-tool` baraye karkardan ba device-haye USB dar mode DFU (Device Firmware Upgrade) be kar miravad. In dastoor komak mikonad firmware ra update ya flash konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dfu-tool --list` --> 🔍 List kardan device-haye DFU motevassel.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --download <file.bin>` --> ⬇️ Firmware ra rooye device download mikonad.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --upload <file.bin>` --> ⬆️ Firmware ra az device upload mikonad.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --reset` --> 🔄 Device ra reset mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dfu-tool --list

    🔹 List kardan hame device-haye DFU ke motevassel hastand.

    $ dfu-tool --download firmware.bin

    🔹 Firmware ra az file `firmware.bin` rooye device DFU download mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dfu-tool --download new_firmware.bin --reset

    🔹 Firmware jadid ra download mikonad va device ra reset mikonad ta firmware jadid ejra shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dfu-tool` command is used to interact with USB devices in DFU (Device Firmware Upgrade) mode.  It helps you update or flash firmware onto devices.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dfu-tool --list` --> 🔍 List connected DFU devices.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --download <file.bin>` --> ⬇️ Download firmware to the device.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --upload <file.bin>` --> ⬆️ Upload firmware from the device.
    🔹 `dfu-tool --reset` --> 🔄 Reset the device.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dfu-tool --list

    🔹 List all connected DFU devices.

    $ dfu-tool --download firmware.bin

    🔹 Download the firmware from the `firmware.bin` file to the DFU device.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dfu-tool --download new_firmware.bin --reset

    🔹 Downloads the new firmware and resets the device so that the new firmware runs.
